# ZIslamicApp QA Context

## App Under Test

Multi-module Android wallet app (`:presentation`, `:domain`, `:data`, `:common`).

## High-Risk Areas (Always Test)

- **Auth** — login, OTP, PIN, session expiry, device change, biometric
- **Payments / Send Money** — amount validation, double-submit, transaction state
- **QR Payment / Merchant** — camera permissions, scan failures
- **Card Management** — activation, issuance, sensitive card data
- **Balance / Mini Statement** — show/hide balance, stale data, API failures
- **Navigation** — deep links, back stack, shared ViewModel scope (`activitySharedHiltViewModel` vs graph-scoped)
- **Network** — `BaseRepository.safeApiCall`, VPN check, offline, timeout (90s read)
- **Localization** — Urdu (RTL/Jameel font) vs English (Outfit)

## Cross-Verification Workflow

After any `@android-principal` implementation, run `@android-qa-engineer` on the same changes before PR.

| Step | Agent | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| 1 | `@android-principal` | Implement feature/fix |
| 2 | `@android-qa-engineer` | Independent QA validation (all 7 phases) |
| 3 | `@android-code-reviewer` | Architecture/code review |
| 4 | Release decision | QA Release Decision gates merge |

Dev and QA agents are **independent**. QA must not defer to dev assumptions.

## API Testing Notes

- Dynamic endpoints via `UrlProvider` / `EndPointsKey`
- Errors via `ResponseStates.Failure` — verify user-facing messages use `getStringLocale()`
- Interceptors handle auth headers — verify session expiry paths

## Regression Hotspots

- Dashboard (`DashboardNavigation.kt`, `DashboardViewModel`)
- Bottom tab navigation (`BottomTabs`)
- Shared ViewModels across features (SendMoney, Payment, Telco, Auth)
- `savedStateHandle` / `ParamUtils` navigation args
